================
Write Java Code
================

- Class
  - Nameing rules
    - Alphanumberic
    - Starts with alphabet
  - Each java file must contain a class
  - Java file is same as java class name

- Method
  - Set of instructions wihch we want to execute
  - Declared inside a class body
  - We cannot declare a method outside a class body

  - main() method
    - java starts execution of the program from main() method

- Statement
  - executable instuction in java
  - ends with semi-column(;)
  - statements are executed from left to Right

- Comments 
  - /*  lines of cade  */

- Sample Class Structure
  public class MyClass{
    public static void main(String[] args){
      //code
    }
  }
  

